The paper also discusses cache oblivious algorithms, which are a type of algorithm design technique that falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.AL). Additionally, the paper involves analyzing the I/O complexity of the algorithms, which is a topic in the area of algorithms for external memory (cs.DM). The paper also mentions the use of binary trees, which is a topic in the area of combinatorics and computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper discusses the practical performance of the algorithms, which is a topic in the area of computer architecture and embedded systems (cs.AT).
